Based on your answers you may need to update the tracking code to use the correct parameters for v3 version. In v3, HubSpot uses utm_source and utm_medium parameters to track the original source of leads. You can use these parameters to differentiate between Google and Facebook leads by setting a more specific utm_medium value for each source, such as google-organic or facebook-paid.

If it helps here is an example tracking code if it helps let me know:

const utmSource = 'utm_source';
const utmMedium = 'utm_medium';

const originalSourceDrillDown2 = `${utmSource}=google&amp;${utmMedium}=google-organic`;
const facebookOriginalSourceDrillDown2 = `${utmSource}=facebook&amp;${utmMedium}=facebook-paid`;

window.HubSpotTracking = {
  track: {
    originalSource: 'google',
    originalSourceData2: originalSourceDrillDown2
  }
};

window.HubSpotTracking = {
  track: {
    originalSource: 'facebook',
    originalSourceData2: facebookOriginalSourceDrillDown2
  }
};
